messages.content:
Generate a complete launch content pack for:

Launch: {{ $json.launch_name }}
GitHub: {{ $json.github_url }}
Key feature: {{ $json.key_feature }}
Honest limitation: {{ $json.honest_limitation }}
HN question: {{ $json.question_for_hn }}

Return a JSON object with these keys:
{
  "hn_title": "Show HN: title under 80 chars",
  "hn_body": "3-5 paragraph HN post, problem-first, honest, ends with question",
  "twitter_thread": ["tweet 1 (opener)", "tweet 2", "tweet 3", "tweet 4 (CTA)"],
  "reddit_post": {"title": "...", "body": "..." },
  "newsletter_subject": "email subject line",
  "newsletter_preview": "first 2 paragraphs of launch newsletter"
}

Return only the JSON, no surrounding text.

parameters.functionCode:
const raw = $input.first().json.content[0].text;
const content = JSON.parse(raw);
return [{ json: { ...content, launch_data: $('webhook-trigger').first().json } }];
